<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Would=C2=A0<em>you=C2=A0</em>want to buy Silic=
on Valley Bank? You get three main things:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">A big portfolio of Treasury bonds and=
 agency mortgage-backed securities. These are worth what they=E2=80=99re wo=
rth: There=E2=80=99s a pretty liquid market for them and not much dispute a=
bout their value. They=E2=80=99re worth a lot less than SVB paid for them, =
which is a big part of why SVB failed last week, but they=E2=80=99re worth =
a lot more today than they were last week,=C2=A0<em>because=C2=A0</em>SVB f=
ailed and so everyone panicked and rushed to buy safe assets like Treasurie=
s.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">A portfolio of loans. The <a hr=
ef=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30845777.258426/aHR0cHM=
6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDMtMTAvc3RhcnR1cC=
1iYW5rLWhhZC1hLXN0YXJ0dXAtYmFuay1ydW4_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDMxNTIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmd=
XRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwMzE1JnV0=
bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZmI2Zvb3Rub3RlLTI/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBbe9083=
f5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">  loans</a> <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com=
/click/30845777.258426/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRh=
LzcxOTczOS8wMDAxMTkzMTI1MjMwNjQ2ODAvZDQzMDkyMGRleDk5Mi5odG0/607f07ceef4b852=
4a319a23cB381d2cad" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;"> are</a> frankly pretty cool? If you buy this=
 portfolio you will have a lot of mortgages on fancy vineyards? And on a lo=
t of tech execs=E2=80=99 fancy houses? But also you will have a big book of=
 capital-call financing for venture capital firms, a bit of financial engin=
eering that seems to produce safe loans. Also a smaller book of loans to ri=
sky startups.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"colo=
r: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bor=
der-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background=
-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">A, look, somewhat tarnished, but =
still interesting=C2=A0<em>brand=C2=A0</em>and set of=C2=A0<em>relationship=
s</em>. Silicon Valley Bank was the leading bank of the huge and exciting e=
cosystem of startups and venture capitalists, until the VCs all turned on i=
t last week out of boredom and=C2=A0a desire for Twitter clout. But they=E2=
=80=99re sorry for what they did and have promised to come back to SVB and =
support it, and maybe that=E2=80=99s worth something. SVB was the cool bank=
 for tech startups, and maybe if you buy it=C2=A0<em>you=C2=A0</em>can be t=
he cool bank for tech startups?</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Those are the main things, but you could imagi=
ne other, more contingent things. Like: If you buy SVB, and it turns out to=
 have been up to bad stuff, do you get sued for the bad stuff? That would b=
e bad. Conversely: If you buy SVB out of government receivership, taking it=
 off the hands of the Federal Deposit Insurance Corp., can you get the FDIC=
 to do some sort of risk-sharing where if those Treasuries lose more value,=
 or if=C2=A0all the loans turn out to be bad, the FDIC will reimburse you f=
or some of the loss? All sorts of possibilities.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t know if you should buy SVB?=C2=
=A0The first thing you get, the securities portfolio, seems pretty easy to =
value, though there are a lot of them and they=E2=80=99d take some time to =
sell so you=E2=80=99d have some risk. The second thing, the loan book, seem=
s harder. SVB was in a business of making somewhat nontraditional loans to =
somewhat nontraditional borrowers and your average regional bank might not =
know what to do with them. Some of these loans, to early-stage startups, wi=
ll probably look alarming to traditional banks. Some of them, loans to vent=
ure capital funds secured by those funds=E2=80=99 limited partners=E2=80=99=
 capital commitments, will probably look pretty sweet. I have no idea about=
 the vineyards.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The third thing you get, the franchise and rel=
ationships, looked great a year=C2=A0ago when the tech industry was booming=
. It looked pretty good a week ago, when the tech industry was slumping but=
 still prominent and profitable. But I think that <a href=3D"https://link.m=
ail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30845777.258426/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJ=
nLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDMtMTAvc3RhcnR1cC1iYW5rLWhhZC1hLXN0YX=
J0dXAtYmFuay1ydW4_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDMxNTIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpb=
CZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwMzE1JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25l=
eXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBaed5feec" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscop=
e=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration:=
 none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; b=
order-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  the story of SVB=E2=
=80=99s failure</a> has turned out to be that SVB was the banker=C2=A0to te=
ch startups, and tech startups turned out to be incredibly dangerous custom=
ers for a bank.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"co=
lor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; b=
order-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; backgrou=
nd-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>=C2=A0So any other bank will have to be careful about acquiring SVB=E2=
=80=99s customers, no matter how loyal they are promising to be now. You mi=
ght ascribe a=C2=A0<em>negative=C2=A0</em>value to those relationships: =E2=
=80=9CIf I become the bank of venture capitalists, they will push me to do =
stuff that is not in my best interests, and I will be seduced or pressured =
and say yes, so the expected value of these relationships is negative.=E2=
=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway, the FDIC took over Silicon Valley Bank=
 last Friday, and then spent the weekend trying to sell it. I assumed it wo=
uld succeed, because I still thought the=C2=A0franchise was valuable, and b=
ecause I remember the experience of 2008 when Jamie Dimon seemed to spend e=
very weekend buying failed banks. But it failed: Presumably the FDIC will e=
ventually sell SVB, in whole or in pieces, but the neat solution of selling=
 it as a whole on Sunday and opening it up on Monday as a normal bank faile=
d. Instead,=C2=A0the FDIC and the Fed had to announce extraordinary measure=
s to guarantee deposits at SVB and to lend cash to other regional banks so =
that=C2=A0<em>they=C2=A0</em>don=E2=80=99t have runs.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is a lot of reporting about why the FDIC=
 failed to sell SVB. One reason does seem to be that Jamie Dimon is no long=
er in the buying-failed-banks-every-weekend business, because he is still a=
ggrieved about how that worked out in 2008. At the Information, <a href=3D"=
https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30845777.258426/aHR0cHM6Ly93d=
3cudGhlaW5mb3JtYXRpb24uY29tL2FydGljbGVzL2hvdy1qcG1vcmdhbi1tYW5ldXZlcmVkLWR1=
cmluZy10aGUtZmFsbC1vZi1zaWxpY29uLXZhbGxleS1iYW5rP3JjPTFiZGk1aA/607f07ceef4b=
8524a319a23cBf7a5ec8f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" targe=
t=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bor=
der-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: s=
olid; background-color: #ccc;"> Lauren Tara LaCapra and Michael Roddan repo=
rt</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">JPMorgan didn=E2=80=99t show up as an emergenc=
y lender to SVB and didn=E2=80=99t bid on SVB after the bank failed and cam=
e up for government auction, the people said. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Lessons from the financial crisis are still se=
ared into management=E2=80=99s brain at JPMorgan. After the 2008 crisis, it=
 got slapped with the label of a bailed-out bank profiting from taxpayers=
=E2=80=99 generosity, and it eventually paid billions of dollars of fines a=
nd legal expenses after buying Bear Stearns and Washington Mutual, includin=
g a then-record $13 billion penalty over mortgage lending. The irony was th=
at it completed the takeovers partly at the request of the government, whic=
h had encouraged JPMorgan to acquire the stressed banks to prevent further =
instability in the financial system.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">As CEO Jamie Dimon said in his 2018 letter to =
shareholders: =E2=80=9CIn case you were wondering: No, we would not do some=
thing like Bear Stearns again=E2=80=94in fact, I don=E2=80=99t think our bo=
ard would let me take the call.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Is SVB going to owe billions of dollars of set=
tlements over the misdeeds that led to its failure, and will any acquirer b=
e on the hook for those settlements? I mean, my guess is no, but Jamie Dimo=
n doesn=E2=80=99t want to find out.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also, though, it=E2=80=99s not like the FDIC w=
anted him bidding. At Semafor, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusine=
ss.com/click/30845777.258426/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VtYWZvci5jb20vYXJ0aWNsZS8wMy=
8xNC8yMDIzL2xhcmdlc3QtdXMtYmFua3MtZmlyc3Qtc2h1dC1vdXQtb2Ytc2lsaWNvbi12YWxsZ=
XktYmFuay1iaWQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe1b219b2" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" it=
emscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decor=
ation: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000=
000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Liz Hoffman and =
Gina Chon report</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The largest U.S. banks didn=E2=80=99t submit a=
 bid for Silicon Valley Bank over the weekend, largely because they were in=
itially excluded from the sales process by the Federal Deposit Insurance Co=
rp. and ran out of time as a result, people familiar with the matter said.<=
/p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The agency, which is led by FDIC Chair Martin =
Gruenberg, who has been publicly critical of consolidation in the industry,=
 eventually allowed the biggest global banks into the auction where potenti=
al bidders didn=E2=80=99t get access to SVB=E2=80=99s financial information=
 until late into the weekend, when the data room was opened, the people sai=
d.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I think there is a view among financial regula=
tors that it was=C2=A0<em>bad=C2=A0</em>that the 2008 financial crisis incr=
eased concentration in the banking industry, as all the failed banks kept b=
eing bought by giant banks. The regulators would prefer not to repeat that =
history. The problem is that it=E2=80=99s hard for anyone=C2=A0<em>other=C2=
=A0</em>than a giant bank to buy a failed still-pretty-big bank, and if you=
=C2=A0<em>don=E2=80=99t=C2=A0</em>have a buyer then the crisis gets worse a=
nd <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30845777.258426=
/aHR0cHM6Ly9jdXN0b21lcmNlbnRlci53c2ouY29tL3ZpZXcvcGF5bWVudF9tZXRob2RzLmh0bW=
w_Y2NfZmFpbD10cnVlJm5zPXByb2QvYWNjb3VudHMtbXcmdXJsPWh0dHBzJTNBJTJGJTJGd3d3L=
m1hcmtldHdhdGNoLmNvbSUyRnN0b3J5JTJGcmVnaW9uYWwtYmFua3MtYXJlLXNlZWluZy1mbGln=
aHQtb2YtZGVwb3NpdHMtdG8tdG9vLWJpZy10by1mYWlsLW1lZ2FiYW5rcy1lMDcyZGFhNyZ1dWl=
kPWRlNWRjNzhlLTgxNWMtNDY4NC05NDVkLTMwMmYxMzZiMTAzNg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23=
cB6e1035cd" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank=
" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-=
width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backg=
round-color: #ccc;"> depositors flee to the giant banks</a>. As Twitter use=
r Modest Proposal <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/=
30845777.258426/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9tb2Rlc3Rwcm9wb3NhbDEvc3RhdHVzLzE=
2MzUyNTk3ODI4MDU0NTg5NDQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB437b46d1" itemprop=3D"Sto=
ryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; =
text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-c=
olor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> put it=
</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are two main ways to increase concentrat=
ion in the banking sector=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">1. Let big banks acquire troubled banks</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">2. Don=E2=80=99t let big banks acquire trouble=
d banks</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If JPMorgan bought SVB, it would end up with=
=C2=A0all of SVB=E2=80=99s deposits. If no one buys SVB, JPMorgan might als=
o end up with all of SVB=E2=80=99s deposits.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Meanwhile I guess this is <a href=3D"https://l=
ink.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30845777.258426/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW=
1lcy5jb20vMjAyMy8wMy8xNC91cy9wb2xpdGljcy9pbnNpZGUtc2lsaWNvbi12YWxsZXktYmFua=
y1yZXNjdWUuaHRtbA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB292f4321" itemprop=3D"StoryLink"=
 itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-de=
coration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #=
000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> the best the =
FDIC got</a>?</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One large regional bank, PNC, tipt=
oed toward making an acceptable offer. But that deal fell through as the ba=
nk scrambled to scrub Silicon Valley Bank=E2=80=99s books and failed to get=
 enough assurances from the government that it would be protected from risk=
s, according to a person briefed on the matter.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One lesson that Jamie Dimon learned in 2008 wa=
s that if you buy a big failed bank you might eventually get sued for its f=
ailings, but another lesson banks learned in 2008 was that if you buy a big=
 failed bank over the weekend you can reasonably say to the government =E2=
=80=9Cokay, well, I=E2=80=99ve had 20 minutes to do due diligence, but if a=
ny of these bonds go down will you pay me back for my losses,=E2=80=9D and =
the government might say yes. PNC Financial Services Group=C2=A0apparently =
tried that, but the government didn=E2=80=99t bite.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Arguably one lesson that the=C2=A0<em>governme=
nt=C2=A0</em>learned in 2008 was that that was dumb: Why sell a failed bank=
 to a buyer, give the buyer the upside, and give the government the downsid=
e? By not hitting PNC=E2=80=99s bid, the FDIC kept all of the downside of S=
VB and its portfolio, but it also kept all of the upside. Not forever, I me=
an =E2=80=94=C2=A0presumably it will sell SVB pretty soon =E2=80=94=C2=A0bu=
t because the government was willing to float SVB for longer than a weekend=
, it was not desperate to accept PNC=E2=80=99s offer, and may end up doing =
a lot better. Or worse, but, again, rates have rallied a lot since last wee=
k.</p>
