<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">As I said above, the basic story=C2=A0of the f=
all of SVB is that venture-backed tech startups plowed too much money into =
SVB too quickly in the boom times, and took it out too quickly last week. S=
VB had nowhere to put that money except in long-dated government bonds with=
 lots of interest-rate risk; when rates went up those bonds lost money, and=
 when its depositors all fled last week it realized those losses and went b=
ust. The depositors were the problem.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But, as a former equity capital markets banker=
 at Goldman Sachs Group Inc. (disclosure!), I should add that another story=
 of the fall of SVB is that Goldman=E2=80=99s equity capital markets advice=
 might not have been that hot? Here is a pretty brutal review from former c=
apital markets banker=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.c=
om/click/30845777.258426/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvN2U3ZmRkZGItNz=
I0Yy00MmZkLTk4ZWUtNWQ3MjQ4ZDUzMzM0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB4f138d79" itemp=
rop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color:=
 #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; borde=
r-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc=
;"> Craig Coben at FT Alphaville</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Couldn=E2=80=99t SVB have saved itself?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">After all, SVB had put together a rescue plan =
with a powerhouse investment bank and a powerhouse investment firm. On the =
evening of March 8 SVB launched a $2.25bn combined common and preferred sto=
ck offering led by Goldman Sachs, with General Atlantic agreeing to purchas=
e $500mn of the common stock at the offer price.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Better yet, SVB was raising more money than th=
e $1.8bn it said it had lost from the sale of nearly all of its =E2=80=9Cav=
ailable for sale=E2=80=9D (AfS) bond portfolio. What could go wrong?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Everything.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Coben explains how you should do it<a class=3D=
"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-4" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorat=
ion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00000=
0; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !imp=
ortant; display: inline-block;">
<span>[4]</span>
</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">First, go big. Really big. Bazooka-big. Raise =
a lot more equity than you need and a lot more equity than regulators tell =
you to raise. Don=E2=80=99t just fill in the capital hole.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Second, the stock offering has to be underwrit=
ten. Hard-underwritten. Or already subscribed-for. Investors must assess th=
e equity offering on the basis of a repaired balance sheet. They must know =
you don=E2=80=99t actually need them.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That is, if you go out and announce =E2=80=9Ch=
ey we=E2=80=99d like to raise $2 billion of equity, anyone interested?=E2=
=80=9D everyone will panic and (1) not buy the stock and (2) withdraw depos=
its, cause a run, etc. But if you go out and announce =E2=80=9Chey we have =
already raised $5 billion of equity, everything=E2=80=99s cool now,=E2=80=
=9D then everything will in fact be cool.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This advice seems fine, but it=C2=A0does assum=
e that you=C2=A0<em>can=C2=A0</em>go out and raise a ton of equity before p=
ublicly announcing the deal. If you can do that =E2=80=94=C2=A0if you can q=
uietly call half a dozen big investors and get them all to agree to write $=
500+ million checks and then announce =E2=80=9Cour deal is done, everything=
=E2=80=99s great,=E2=80=9D then great. A lot of bank rescues=C2=A0<em>have=
=C2=A0</em>gone like that. But there=E2=80=99s no guarantee it will work, a=
nd SVB didn=E2=80=99t have a ton of time to find out.<a class=3D"footnote-i=
ndex" href=3D"#footnote-5" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !=
important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-b=
ottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; dis=
