; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Bloomberg News reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The death spiral at SVB began with credit rati=
ngs. In early March, Moody=E2=80=99s informed the bank it was considering a=
 multilevel downgrade that would have pushed it to the brink of junk-bond s=
tatus. In response, Goldman Sachs Group Inc., hired by SVB to help it raise=
 fresh capital, jumped into action. It offloaded a chunk of SVB=E2=80=99s i=
nvestment portfolio at a $1.8 billion loss. On Wednesday, March 8, Goldman =
pitched a plan to investors to help plug that hole, and then some, by raisi=
ng $2.25 billion in capital from General Atlantic and other investors. It d=
idn=E2=80=99t work.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThe Catch-22 of the situation is that=
, by announcing the need to raise capital, they in essence accelerated cust=
omer concern, resulting in the liquidity stress that ultimately caused thei=
r collapse,=E2=80=9D says Olivier Sarkozy, managing partner at Further Glob=
al, a private equity firm. =E2=80=9CIt would have been far better to announ=
ce the $2.25 billion they were seeking had been secured.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the bankers=E2=80=99 view, they were racing=
 the clock to defuse the Moody=E2=80=99s threat. That didn=E2=80=99t leave =
them enough time to canvass the market, line up the funding and present a n=
eatly put-together deal.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Obviously announcing the capital raise=C2=A0<e=
m>without </em>having=C2=A0buyers lined up led to a disaster, but announcin=
g a Moody=E2=80=99s downgrade without any capital raise would also have led=
