mportant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bo=
ttom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">and</a>:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">25.5% of the common stock voted to aut=
horize more shares, 9.1% voted no, 0.5% abstained (like, affirmatively chos=
e to vote, but marked =E2=80=9Cabstain=E2=80=9D) and the other 64.8% just d=
idn=E2=80=99t vote.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">57.1% of the A=
PES voted yes, 5.2% no, 0.5% abstained and 37.3% didn=E2=80=99t vote.</li>=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">But because of the preferred-stock vot=
ing mechanic, that meant that 91% of the preferred stock voted yes, 8.3% no=
 and 0.7% abstained, making for more than enough votes to authorize the new=
 shares.</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">AMC <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/30845777.258426/aHR0cHM6Ly9pbnZlc3Rvci5hbWN0aGVhdHJlcy5jb20v=
bmV3c3Jvb20vbmV3cy1kZXRhaWxzLzIwMjMvQU1DLUVudGVydGFpbm1lbnQtSG9sZGluZ3MtSW5=
jLi1Bbm5vdW5jZXMtUmVzdWx0cy1vZi1TcGVjaWFsLU1lZXRpbmctb2YtU3RvY2tob2xkZXJzL2=
RlZmF1bHQuYXNweA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB064ca6ef" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" =
itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-dec=
oration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0=
00000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">said</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Commenting on the results, Adam Ar=
on, AMC Entertainment Chairman and CEO said, =E2=80=9CAMC=E2=80=99s shareho=
lders exercised their rights today to have their voices be heard. They vote=
d resoundingly in favor of proposals that we believe are crucial to AMC=E2=
=80=99s future. Shareholders overwhelmingly approved combining AMC common s=
hares and APE units, with total votes 87% in favor, while significantly inc=
reasing the capacity to issue additional common shares, with total votes 88=
% in favor.If implemented, AMC should have an ability to raise a significan=
t amount of equity capital in the months and years ahead. Winning these sha=
reholder votes by such a lopsided margin is a powerful vote of confidence t=
o allow AMC to raise equity capital, reduce debt, strengthen our balance sh=
eet and continue our transformation.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And I think it has a good argument in court th=
at the shareholders=C2=A0<em>did=C2=A0</em>vote in favor of authorizing new=
 shares, to the extent they voted at all, so the APE mechanism was a way to=
 give shareholders what they wanted even though the shareholders never vote=
. Again I am not=C2=A0<em>sure=C2=A0</em>that a Delaware court will allow i=
t: The APEs kicked off a wave of strange voting preferred stock deals desig=
ned to get around shareholder voting problems, and the court might reasonab=
ly think =E2=80=9Cwe don=E2=80=99t want boards of directors to engineer sha=
reholder votes like this so we=E2=80=99re going to block the APEs.=E2=80=9D=
 But, again, it would be a bit harsh, because the APEs really do seem to be=
 giving AMC shareholders what they want.</p>
